# TeleHealthy Deploy-Test

## Test environment
- Playwright 1.61.0 / Chromium headless
- Live URLs: `https://michaelwegter.com/demos/telehealthy/` + `https://api.michaelwegter.com/health`

---

## Test results

### T1 — Work-samples SPA route
`https://michaelwegter.com/work-samples/telehealthy`
- Page title: "TeleHealthy Voice Ops Console — Michael Wegter" ✓
- `<iframe src="/demos/telehealthy/">` present ✓

### T2 — Demo direct load
`https://michaelwegter.com/demos/telehealthy/`
- Title: "TeleHealthy Voice Ops Console" ✓
- Hero heading: "Inbound Voice Ops Console" ✓
- No page errors, no failed resources ✓
- Note: initial load produced 1 transient console 404 (no URL captured; repeat runs show 0 failed responses — likely WebGPU model availability probe or favicon; non-blocking)

### T3 — Inbound booking hero flow
1. "Simulate Inbound Call" button → clicked ✓
2. Intent buttons appear: Book / Hours / Insurance / Telehealth / **This is urgent** / End Call ✓
3. "Book an appointment" → AI confidence 88%, phase advances to `📅 BOOK APPT` ✓
4. "New Patient" chip → AI responds with follow-up prompt ✓
5. SMS LOG section visible in sidebar ✓
6. Multi-step booking conversation flow works as scripted ✓

### T4 — Warm-transfer path
1. "This is urgent" chip → call status changes to **TRANSFERRING** ✓
2. AI confidence drops to 34% (🚨 ESCALATE badge appears) ✓
3. AI message: "Let me connect you with one of our care coordinators right away. Please hold." ✓
4. 🚨 CARE COORDINATOR escalation marker shown in transcript ✓

### T5 — Tab navigation
| Tab | Content | Notes |
|-----|---------|-------|
| 📤 Outbound | CRM CONTACTS (8 patients) | Maria Santos, James Whitfield, Sofia Reyes, David Kim + 4 more ✓ |
| 👥 CRM | Patient table (8 rows, insurance/provider/visit/appt columns) ✓ | |
| 📊 Analytics | 155 total calls, 67% booking rate, 8% escalation rate, 0.79 avg confidence, 2m14s avg handle time ✓ | |

### T6 — API health
`https://api.michaelwegter.com/health` → 200 `{"status":"ok","version":"1.0.0"}` ✓
(Demo is frontend-only; no Flask blueprint needed)

### T7 — Skipped paths
- WebGPU / WebLLM Llama 3.2 1B load: skipped per deploy handoff (GPU-only, headless non-testable)
- Language toggle (EN/ES): present in UI, functional test deferred (non-hero)

